This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and machine translation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new model for neural machine translation. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques for language translation. The paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which could place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the use of Chinese-English translation, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as Chinese characters are often used in computer vision tasks.
